review_blob: Hazy brown color with white head. Aroma is smoky ham. Taste is smoky ham,with a weird fruity flavour and some wet dog. Not excellent.
Tap. Hazy orange color with white head. Aroma is tart fruits, some lacto. Taste is quite sour, peach?, some lacto. Low carbonation. Palate cleanser, damn. Not bad though.
Can. Beautiful clear amber color with nice beige head. Aroma is mango, some rye spiciness. Taste is sweet mango, toasted malts, caramel, pines. Bittersweet finish. Soft carbonation. Good stuff.

Bottle. Black color with beige head. Aroma is coffee, milk chocolate, lacto. Taste is lacto, coffee, coffee, coffee, slightly metallic. Super-silky oat mouthfeel. Light-bodied, but not watery. Very good.

Bottle.Hazy pale yellow color with small head that goes down quickly. Aroma is elderflower, grassy hops, some red apples. Taste is grassy hops, red apples, dusty, slightly tanninic. Fizzy carbonation. Rather sweet. Not bad.
Deep copper color with white head. Aroma is pink grapefruit, fruity, not too hoppy. Taste is pink grapefruit, tart, refreshing. Some light toasted malts. Light. Low carbonation. Good.
Bottle. Clear amber color with tan head. Aroma is caramel, wiener malt. Taste is light caramel, grainy, metallic. Not bad, but nothing special either.

Bottle. Clear golden color with white head. Aroma is straw, spicy, a bit hoppy, a touch of butter. Taste is a bit of dough, grassy, crisp. Slightly full-bodied. Refreshing. Quite good for a Premium Lager.

Can from a trade with sneakychi, many thanks! Pitch black color with beige head. Aroma is black chocolate, coffee, some roastiness, a bit spicy (chili-like). Taste is roasted malts, black chocolate, spicy chili catch, quite dry for this ABV, but also quite yeasty imho. Amazing balance, it?s light and dry while staying full and rich. A masterpiece of non-overwhelming ImpStout - complex and with a certain sessionability without feeling weak, which is very rare for ImpStouts. Great stuff in its own way. But its definitely different from most 100-percentile-ImpStouts, which are usually way thicker, and different from what Id expected.

Bottle as Soft DK. Black color with small beige head. Aroma is sweet milk chocolate, some raisins. Taste is raisins, chocolate, iron, liver, some vanilla. Quite light for the ABV, so the ABV is definitely well-hidden. Still good. Not excellent for a ImpStout.

Bottle. Hazy copper color with nice white head. Aroma is piney, grassy, and some older hop flavours, also a bit spicy, toffee and doughy yeast. Taste is spicy, piney, a hint of metal and iron, but not exactly oxidized, some more dough. Some slight off flavours, heavily bitter finish. Nice aroma, okay taste. High fine-bubbled carbonation. Alright.

Bottle. Hazy golden-orange color with small white head. Aroma is melon, caramel, piney-resinous hop oils. Taste is sweet toasty malts, caramel, piney, soothing. Bittersweet finish, but on the drier side for this pineyness. Fine-bubbled carbonation. A correct "woodfloor" IPA.

Bottle. Dark brown color with beige head. Aroma is chocolate, oat, quite intense. Taste is chocolate, oat, some green peppers, leather, nutty, light and refreshing. A bit too light after this intense aroma. Fine-bubbled carbonation. Sweetish, but not really sweet and a little bit too watery. Quite light actually. Good.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Barney Flats Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Amber color with white head. Aroma is soft buttery, an idea of a fruitiness there. Not the bad way of butter. Taste is buttery, a fudgy malt body, bitter finish, a bit shalloty. Lightly bitter finish, a hint of a tartness as well. Full-bodied buttery mouthfeel with fine-bubbled carbonation. Pleasant, but not hoppy-fruity enough. Interesting take on an IPA. I usually find butteryness unpleasant, but this is fine.
UPDATED: APR 28, 2016

Bottle. Brown color with reddish highlight and a beige head. Aroma is bananas, cloves, dark bread, toffee. Taste is bready, malty, spicy yeasts, raisins, a bit sweet and chocolaty. Aroma is good, taste is a bit weak. Silky mouthfeel, low carbonation. All in all not bad though.

Bottle. Hazy golden color with creamy white head. For the aroma, "lemondrop" isnt even far off - its got an artificial sweet lemony aroma, cleaning agent like. Also a bit spicy-peppery and dill. Quite ethereous, like a Gletschereis bonbon. Flavour is there, but I find it a bit unpleasant. Taste is spicy, with fresh yeast, candied lemon, a bit sugary and herbal. Heavy-bodied, medium carbonation. Not a Tripel - not at all. And not a very good beer either, if you ask me, the etherealness is too medical and gives the beer a ridiculous unbalancedness..

Bottle, 7.7% version, thanks Jonas! Oh boy, a Malt Likka. Lets see. Pouring while still cold. Golden color with small creamy white head. Aroma is wet paper, straw, corn, raisins, syrupy booze, starch. Taste is surprisingly tart, wet cardboard and straw, warming alcohol, grainy sweetness, and a stingy boozy finish. Low to medium carbonation. Not a lot of fun, but not exactly terrible (yet - at least while being cold, but the off flavours already start showing up).

Hazy golden-yellow color with white head. Aroma is buttery, a bit fruity hops, but for me, lots of butter. Taste is buttery and fruity again, going into a bitter hoppy finish. Medium carbonation. Too buttery, and it doesnt work out completely, but it hides the ABV well and has nice aspects.
beer_name: Marina / Het Nest Full Of Hops

review_blob: Black color with small tan ring. Aroma is coffee, lacto, cocoa powder. Taste is coffee, milk chocolate, lacto sweetness, but with a dry finish. Near-flat. Nice.
Clear golden color with small white head. Aroma is sweet hops. Taste is bitter, some off flavours that are hard to describe, with a weird spiciness. Low carbonation. Meh, not my kind of beer.

Bottle. Pale golden color with creamy white head. Aroma is sweet pale malts, butter, slightly earthy noble hops. Taste is butter, earthy, bubblegum, sweet round pale malt body. Light-bodied. Convincing if you like the Franconian butteryness. I do like it more here than in Pale Ales. EDIT: I like it more and more with every sip. Off-topic: I am baffled: My favourite Single Malt is Caol Ila - its buttery. I also like buttery Landbier and Czech Pils. But why dont I like buttery Pale Ales? Maybe the aggressive modern fruitiness doesnt work out with butteryness.

Bottle. Dark brown color with beige head. Aroma is ripe bananas, yeast, berries, some toasted bread. Taste is ripe bananas, burnt caramel, prunes, toasty, slightly roasted towards the end. Hints of a sourishness that give it a surprisingly light character. Silky Weizen mouthfeel. A great dark Weizenbock with a nice balance. And I have finally found another good example of this beautiful style after a few mediocre ones.

Bottle. Clear golden-orange color with white head. Aroma is slightly dusty, caramel malt, honey, also slightly herbal. Taste is honey, caramel malt, herbal (Kruterbonbon), rather sweet. Finish is aromatic. Medium carbonation. Good flavour for a Heller Bock, but overall a bit thin.
Hazy copper-golden color with white head. Aroma is slightly hoppy, toasted malts. Taste is the same, with quite a bitterness in the finish. Smoked ham towards the end as well. Ok.
Dark brown color with beige head. Aroma is wood sugar, booze, chocolate. Taste is more wood sugar, fruits, caramel, booze. Medium carbonation. Good!
beer_name: Inglorious Quad Whisky Barrel Aged - batch 1 Belgian Owl

review_blob: Hazy golden color with white head. Aroma is flowery, cookie dough, typical Belgian. Taste is more cookie dough and floral hops, with a grain sweetness and a slightly bitter finish. Not bad.
Tap. Hazy orange color with white head. Aroma is apple funk, sugars, apple skin. Taste is more apple funk, boozy, phenolic, full-bodied and oily mouthfeel. Low carbonation. Good.
beer_name: Hof Ten Dormaal Barrel Aged Calvados

review_blob: Brown color with tan head. Aroma is sugary malts, chocolate, no smoke yet. Taste is brown sugar, chocolate, just a hint of smoke in the back. Medium carbonation. Ok.

At Nacht van de Grote Dorst 2016 as "Walnoten Lambik". Hazy golden color with hardly any head. Aroma is nutty, bitter, with nice citric lambic funk. Taste is nutty, citric funk, metallic towards the end. Alright.

Bottle. Quite hazy orange color with white head. Aroma is pink grapefruit, quite tart, very fruity. Taste is pink grapefruit, lacto, sour mash, not very bitter finish. High big-bubbled carbonation. A nice tart and juicy Fruit IPA!
Hazy orange color with small white head. Aroma is red apples, woody. Taste is apples, some more wood sugar, quite full-bodied. Low carbonation. Good.

Brown color with beige head. Aroma is dark malts, a bit coffee and cocoa powder. Taste is bitter chocolate, a bit coffee, a bit of a rye spiciness. Medium carbonation. Rather dry. Sweet is different. Still a fine brew.
Hazy golden color with white head. Aroma is yeast freshness, wheat, bananas. Taste is the same. Quite wheaty. Oily mouthfeel. Not bad though.
Hazy yellow color with white head. Aroma is spicy yeasts, bread dough, bananas. Taste is spicy (special spices), doughy. Interesting.

Hazy golden color with white head. Aroma is sweet fruits, some yeasts, some grassiness. Taste is dough and malts, nice sweet fruits (apricots, peaches). High carbonation, but also an oily mouthfeel. Good enough.
beer_name: t Kroontje Rebelle Tripel - Limited Ed. 2016 Simcoe Hop

review_blob: Amber-brown color with tan head. Aroma is sweet malts, some apples. Taste is not very refined, just a bit of Belgian yeasts and not much maltiness. Lacking character.
Brown color with beige head. Aroma is roasted malts, coffee. Taste is roasted malts, coffee, some butter. Medium carbonation. Hmm... flavour is there, but it doesnt quite work out.
Bottle. Hazy yellow color with white head. Aroma is oat, flowery, typical Belgian blonde.Taste is flowery, sweet dough. Medium carbonation. Ok.

Purple color with white head. Aroma is sweet dough, phenols, syrupy cherry. Taste is dough, phenolic, apples. Medium carbonation. Sweet finish. Not terrible, but I dont get Tripel Kriek as a style. De Leite is the only one Ive liked so far...
Cloudy orange color with white head. Aroma is spicy yeasts, apples, floral. Taste is spicy, tart, wheat, dry finish. Overcarbonated, unfortunately. The apple-ness feels off. Not great.
Hazy golden color with white head. Aroma is fruity, hoppy, orange, peach. Taste is sweet, peach, low carbonation. Medium carbonation, but a bit light-bodied. Good.
beer_name: De Kale Ridders Tumulus Experiment X

review_blob: Brown color with tan head. Aroma is roasted malts, some cat piss. Taste is roasted malts, cocoa, a sweetish fruitiness as well. Not much whisky noticeable. Low carbonation. Good beer, but the Whisky is *very* reluctant.
Orange-golden color with white head. Aroma is cookie dough, Belgian yeasts. Taste is fruity, peaches, apricots, more cookie dough, and a slightly spicy finish. Low carbonation. Ok.
Clear golden color with white head. Aroma is tropical fruits, cat piss. Taste is slightly hoppy. Low carbonation. Ok.
Hazy yellow color with white head. Aroma is citrus candy, some yeasts. Taste is wheat, citrus candy, sweet. Meh. Too American for my taste with that citrus candy.

Hazy orange color with white head. Aroma is sweatsocks, onions, buttery, some blueberry and white wine feeling. Taste is buttery, shallots, dough. Medium carbonation. Has potential, but it has the very common butter flaw I get so often in recent Mosaic brews.
Hazy golden color with small white head. Aroma is estery, apples, slightly phenolic. Taste is more apples, phenolic, high carbonation. Doesnt feel too heavy. Alright.
Brown color with tan head. Aroma is sweet chocolate, some roasted malts. Taste is the same. The weakest of the 3 in the series.
Brown color with tan head. Aroma is roasted, ash, but intensely ashy. Taste is more ash, some sweetness. Oily mouthfeel, more ash in the finish. Damn. Not my kind of beer.
